-- Shares of Turkey's Bank Asya to resume trading at 1100 GMT - exchange
-- By Seda Sezer
-- Wed Sep 24, 2014 06:53AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 24 (Reuters) - Trading in Turkey's Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS>, an Islamic finance institution, will resume at 1100 GMT on Wednesday, the Istanbul stock exchange said in a filing.

The stock will resume trading at a 0.69 lira ($0.31) base price with a 10 percent price margin, the bourse said. The lender's shares were halted on Sept. 18 following volatility in its share price.